==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feudatory
<hw>Feu"da*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Feudatories</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A tenant or vassal who
held his lands of a superior on condition of feudal service; the tenant
of a feud or fief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The grantee . . . was styled the <qex>feudatory</qex> or
vassal.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] had for <qex>feudatories</qex> great princes.</q> <rj><qau>J.
H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feudatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Feudatory
<hw>Feu"da*to*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Held from another on some
conditional tenure; <as>as, a <ex>feudatory</ex> title</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Feu de joie</ent>⟦br⟧
